Line No 7 
           Why do we write <! DOC html>?
           
           
           The line shows that the document is written html5.
           HTML5 is an advanced version of html.
           In html4 there were some slow tags which waste time in loadin and operation
           For example <table> tag was a set of tags [table, tr, td].
           Due to inclusions in the working of audio and video there was no provision in html4
           Similarly, there were many other features were added in the working of internet.

           NOTE: 
                     > The first line on the top, <!DOCTYPE html>, is a document type declaration 
                       and it lets the browser know which flavor of HTML you’re using (HTML5, in this case).

           SO, HTML5 A DEVELOPED VERSION OF HTML TO INCLUDE ALL NEW FEATURES OF INTERNET. 

Line No 8
