 Line No 11  What does the line "<meta http-equiv="X-UA-Compatible" " />"
             indicate?

             The part  of the line shows that 'http-equiv="X-UA-Compatible'
                the code of the document will be Compatible with all kind of output devices-
                computers, laptops, tablets, mobiles or watch mobiles. 

             The part of the line 'content="IE=edge' shows that code will be applicable to IE9
               as we know that 'internet explorer' is not used now 
               only 'IE9' is the latest version.  So, the code will suport 'IE9'.   

